Romance is so important in marriage. To me romance is being brought a coffee in the morning, or my husband making sure that the kids say thank you to me after cooking dinner. He brings me water to my bedside every night and kisses my forehead when he turns off my reading light after I have fallen to sleep. Romance can look like this video, a fancy night out or a bouquet of flowers. But the older I get the more I realize that those things are extras. Those are what we expect romance to look like but it isnt what sustains a relationship in the long run. The most romantic thing in the world is to be truly seen and to be cherished ❤️ #husbandandwife #marriage #marriageadvice #romance #romantic #love #dating #happymarriage

Its world mental health month and I want to talk about Postpartum Anxiety. I had never experienced anxiety before I had my second child and the brick wall of dread that hit me with his birth was the most difficult battle with my mental health I had ever had. I felt like I was suffocating, drowning in my own thoughts and fears, battling intrusive thoughts that mad me want to end it all. If you or someone you know is struggling, know that they did not choose this and that they would wish it away in a heartbeat. But there is help out there! Get your hormones checked! Talk to other mothers! This is more common than you realize and you are not alone ❤️ #postpartummentalhealth #postpartumrecovery #postpartumanxiety #anxiety #maternalmentalhealth #mentalhealthawarenessmonth

A few short weeks before Hurricane Helene we took the kids to visit the Biltmore Estate in Asheville. A beautiful example of architecture and a standing testament to the gilded age of American industrialism. It tells so many stories, not just of the American royalty who lived there but of the place in time that could allow such opulence and excess. It is now a major employer in the city of Asheville, with many jobs and lives depending on the tourism it brings. Western NC is going to need jobs like those back, and the tourism dollars to flow back into the economy once the doors can reopen. Dont count them out just yet. My family and I will be back #asheville #biltmore #biltmoreestate #explorenorthcarolina #visitasheville #hurricanehelene

Our dinner at @ltle.fish.chs blew us out of the water!!! A fairly new concept from the team@that brings us @raw.lab.chs , this menu is redefining the Charleston food scene. With small shareable plates of exquisitely sourced seafood, a flair for theater and an eye for detail, this is a MUST DINE when you’re in town!  . The entire restaurant feels like you are in a Japanese sushi bar under the sea, with a small u-shaped chefs counter covered in crushed ice. Each dish was hand prepared and served beautifully by our chef and guide for the evening.  Stand outs for me were the oysters on the half shell, hand dressed in several different ways to highlight and enhance the oysters flavor profile. The showstopper was definitely the cold smoked oyster which played with our senses of cooked/raw.  I can’t wait to go back! This is the perfect venue for a group dinner, birthday, date night or girls night out!
